.TH "find_any_var_ref" 9 "find_any_var_ref" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
find_any_var_ref \- Check if there is a reference to a given trigger variable
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct hist_field *" find_any_var_ref
.BI "(struct hist_trigger_data *hist_data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int var_idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hist_data" 12
The hist trigger
.IP "var_idx" 12
The trigger variable identifier
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check to see whether the given variable is currently referenced by
any other trigger.

The trigger the variable is defined on is explicitly excluded - the
assumption being that a self-reference doesn't prevent a trigger
from being removed.
.SH "RETURN"
The VAR_REF field referencing the variable if so, NULL if not
